The Air Task Force (ATF) of Operation Lafiya Dole has neutralised several Boko Haram Terrorists (BHTs) and destroyed one of their gun trucks at Bula Korege, a terrorists’ logistics distribution centre and meeting point, on the fringes of the Sambisa Forest in Borno State. The coordinator, Defence Media Operations, Major General John Enenche, said the feat was achieved on 17th June 2020, as part of missions being conducted under the subsidiary Operation LONG REACH, after a Nigerian Air Force (NAF) Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance (ISR) aircraft spotted a large number of BHT fighters and a  gun truck within the settlement. He said consequently, the Air Task Force scrambled its fighter jets to attack the location. “Upon arrival overhead the settlement, the NAF jets engaged the target area, taking out some structures and neutralising some of the terrorists. “The gun truck, while retreating from the location due to the strong firepower from the air, began engaging the attack aircraft with its anti-aircraft gun. “However, the jets, after conducting evasive maneuvres, tracked the vehicle and subsequently immobilised it a few kilometres outside the village. “The occupants of the truck, who attempted to flee, were mopped-up in follow-on attacks by the fighter jets,” he said.